# Trivy ignore list (image scans).
# Each entry MUST include: severity, justification, expiry-or-followup.
# Re-evaluate every time we bump caddy / dependencies.

# === caddy gobinary, frontend image ===========================================
#
# Caddy v2.11.3 binary embeds these third-party libs at the versions caddy's
# go.mod pinned. The vulnerable code paths are NOT reachable in our
# `frontend/Caddyfile.panel`:
#
#   * `auto_https off` — no ACME / no internal CA / no smallstep SCEP;
#   * no `caddyauth` / `jwt` / `oauth` modules — go-jose unreachable;
#   * no Caddy OTel telemetry exporter enabled;
#   * no gRPC reverse-proxy modules.
#
# Caddy upstream ships these libs in their binary regardless of whether the
# affected modules are loaded; we accept the trivy noise until caddy releases
# a binary built against patched deps. Followup: bump caddy version on every
# upstream release; remove entries that disappear from new caddy binary scans.

CVE-2026-34986   # go-jose v3/v4 — JWE DoS; we don't use caddyauth / JWT.
CVE-2026-30836   # smallstep/certificates — SCEP; we have auto_https off.
CVE-2026-29181   # otel baggage header — caddy OTel exporter not enabled.
CVE-2026-39883   # otel SDK PATH hijack — caddy OTel exporter not enabled.
CVE-2026-33186   # grpc-go authz — caddy gRPC reverse-proxy not used.
CVE-2026-33816   # jackc/pgx v5 — caddy postgres-storage module not loaded (default file_storage).
